<br>
Well I do like the /random number number method with the points given at attended raids as mentioned above, but...<br>
<br>
I also think it would make sense to incorporate points for things like.. tradeskills or transportation or even donations to the guild bank/ members... Since, there are more ways than one to improve a guild without raiding. <br>
<br>
A lot of guilds have a few members who do tradeskills and then the rest of the guild benifits off of those few players' investments. Many in-guild tradespeople give these items to guildies at a loss or at equal value to the specific item, minus the failures.   A lot of guilds leave this stuff up to personal choice and such...  However, some guilds have rules that prevent them from making a profit on the items that guildmembers get from them, thus the money they spent to get there is not necessarily recovered.   It would not hurt to encourage all guildies to take up tradeskills.. it not only helps them with some harsh quests, but it lightens the load on those few players who are made responsible for jewel craft/tailoring/smithing/whatever of the guild.  On top of that.. it awards those few people who have been providing the guilds with these services  with a few bonus points before the other people get their trades up.   Even with such a thing.. I doubt that everyone in a guild will work on their tradeskills.<br>
<br>
 I feel really bad for all of those druids/wizards that end up transporting guildies to events then have to log cause their guildies wouldn't just get/pay their own transportation, therefore taking up more time than neccessary -and then they recieve zilch for the time they spent transporting to /participating in the guild function. - and YES.. I do see transportation as a form of participation.  I also see ressurrections/ corpse summonings given as part of the transportation as participation.. these things should not go unawarded.  At most raids I saw,  the transportation recovery team was a druid/wizard and a cleric sometimes, a necromancer or shadowknight. <br>
