<br>
Fact is you will not please everyone ever, whether it is NBG, defaulting, points etc system - each system has its flaws.  <br>
<br>
NBG (Rolls) - this is a good system for a guild that may put on raids very few and far between.  If the guild intends to grow, so will the number of people and the number of raids going on.  <br>
<br>
Ultimately, you will end up with some hardcore raiders in the guild and some that come to some and not to others.  Then you will get the people who will sparsely turn up.  <br>
<br>
Problems arise right here, the people who have been attending raids vigilantly are not getting any benefit for the no.of raids they have attended.  <br>
<br>
By introducing defaulting into the equation with NBG, then you come up with the issue that the people who sparsely/sometimes raid feel penalised for not being there 100% of the time.<br>
<br>
Then comes up with 2 divided factions in the guild those that have given the effort (but maybe not gotten the reward) and those that haven't put in as much effort (but may have got the rewards). <br>
<br>
Defaulting - There are maybe 2 subsections to this - Council Defaulting and Leader defaulting.  <br>
<br>
Council Defaulting - whether it is a static council of say 6 people who vote on when an item drops who gets it or a revolving council, individuals are empowered in the guild to select the most appropriate individual.  <br>
<br>
This is imho a good system, especially if it is a revolving council as it does not give as much preferential treatment as a static council.   In this instance, the revolving council would agree amongst them.  <br>
<br>
In a static council, the same people are used.  The difficulties in this system is that people can and will get preferred over others.  This is very much a system employed by old Wraith - it worked sometimes, it didn't work other times imho.  <br>
<br>
Leader defaulting - be it a raid leader, loot leader, officer or guild leader, by empowering one person to make a decision on these things can be tough.  Purely because one person can make a mistake, he does not know everyone's equipment in the guild and cannot therefore easily say who is best placed.  And of course, it is only one person's opinion. <br>
<br>
Points system - The role reversal of NBG.  This system does have a lot of benefits should it be managed effectively.  The main problem I have seen on the points system is the sheer administration of it all.   People log in, log out - attend raids, dont attend....the administrator has gotta have a nightmare.  What if the administrator is not on, then what ? <br>
<br>
Obviously like a poster said previously, this is more for the raiding type guilds but I feel sorry for the amount of backend work you have to do for it. <br>
<br>
Someone gets their figures mixed up, its all over.  <br>
<br>
Some other consideration you have to take into account...Raiding with other people!.  <br>
<br>
On occasion, you may or may not drafted in /randompeople01 or have a guild alliance.  You have gotta devise a system that attracts people enough to join you, but not enough to penalise your own guildies in the same breath.  <br>
<br>
For instance in a NBG situation, randomcleric01 maybe drafted in for say a HoT raid.  The cleric comes and you hunt in HoT.  A plate BP drops and the randomcleric01 wins it, then bails.  You have as a guild no empowerment to say to the cleric WTF????? and you have pissed off your own guildies in the same breath by not giving them a slight benefit over him.<br>
<br>
An alliance is somewhat different and can be agreed between both parties.<br>
<br>
Just some food for thought as I was working on the positives and negatives of looting systems in EQ, but never found one (that I could use) that was perfect for all concerned. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ffat>Ffat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Village Fatass</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(12/10/02 12:42:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It is probably best....</span><hr size=1> You're still talking out of your ass.<br>
